column20: "Area per family (acres): 1." This can be interpreted as 1 acre per dwelling unit. Since the minimum lot area is already 1 acre, but by the density calculation there would need to be at least 2 acres for a two-family dwelling, default to the higher number.

"For the purposes of section 315 Dwelling includes Accessory Use/Structure when such
Accessory Use/Structure is in harmony with the neighborhood" (Page 16).
"Class 1 lots have both off lot water and sewer. Class 2 lots have either on lot water or on lot sewer. Class 3 lots have both on lot water and on lot sewer" (Page 6).
